 The average age of the Ninja Turtles can be found by using the arithmetic mean, which is calculated by adding all the numbers and then dividing by the count of numbers. In this case, we have two groups (15-year-old turtles and 17-year-old turtles).

<box> \begin{equation*}
\text{{Average Age}} = \frac{\sum\text{{Ages}}}{\text{{Count of Ages}}}
\end{equation*}
</box>

For the Ninja Turtles:

* Sum of ages: 15 (age of first 15-year-old turtle) + 15 (age of second 15-year-old turtle) + 17 (age of first 17-year-old turtle) + 17 (age of second 17-year-old turtle) = 64 years.
* Count of ages: 2 for the 15-year-old turtles + 2 for the 17-year-old turtles = 4 counts in total.

So, <box> \begin{equation*}
\text{{Average Age}} = \frac{64}{4} = 16
\end{equation*}
</box>

Therefore, the average age of the Ninja Turtles is 16 years old.
